<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Equity Prices Soar to New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Greek equity prices surged to
new records Wednesday with the general index on the Athens Stock
Exchange (ASE) ending 3.19 percent higher at 5,371.57 points.
</P>
<P>
This is the 44th record for the ASE general index since the
beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index also jumped 4.04 percent to 2,895.60
points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 429.3 billion drachmas (about 1.38 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 190 to 102 with another 11 issues
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The banks and insurance sectors led the rising stock market
with ending 4.62 percent and 4.02 percent higher respectively.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the stock market was moving towards the
5,600 resistance level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
