<HEADLINE> S. Leone Rebel Leader on Way Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Foday Sankoh, Sierra Leonean
rebel leader, left Togo Wednesday on his way to Freetown, capital
of the west African country, and take the position of Vice
President.
</P>
<P>
However, according to reports reaching here from Togo's capital
Lome, the Leader of the Revolutionary United Front's home journey
is expected to be long.
</P>
<P>
He will visit a number of west African states before appearing
in the country's capital, where he had been kept as a death-
sentence prisoner before the signing of the July 7 Lome peace
agreement.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh apparently quickened his homing pace against a
background that the international community is repeatedly urging
him to go back to help the slack disarming process in the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the BBC before leaving Togo, Sankoh pledged that
his men would respect the agreement scrupulously, despite what he
said Tuesday that he should be cautious since he was not going to
attend a "marriage party". 
</P>
</TEXT>
