<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Culture Week Opens in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The China Culture Week -- `99
Paris was formally opened Wednesday evening here at the United
Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO)
headquarters, on the eve of the 50th anniversary of the founding
of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party (CPC) Central Committee and Minister of Publicity, Frederico
Mayor, Secretary General of UNESCO, and Catherine Trautmann,
French Minister of Culture and Communications, cut the ribbon of
the exhibition hall, where a wide set of objects showing the
history, culture, science, technological and socio-economic
progress of China will be on display until September 12.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was held in the garden of UNESCO building,
which was decorated with many red Chinese flags used for festival
activities, and a giant lion wearing a red costume. About 500
French friends from all walks of life attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the cultural week, jointly held by China and
UNESCO and the biggest ever in Europe, is to help the French
people and other people in the world better know the history and
present of China, its science and art, and its reform and
development, said Zhao Qizheng, the director of Information Office
of the State Council of China.
</P>
<P>
The UNESCO secretary general said that China has an ancient
civilization with a rich culture. He said that the cultural week
will show the world not only China's ancient civilization, but
also its dynamic present.
</P>
<P>
The French minister of culture said that France has long been
fascinated by China's great long-lived culture. She said the
cultural week provides French people with a rare chance to better
understand China's past and present.
</P>
<P>
To make the event a success, China has sent a 320-person
delegation representing government officials, scientists,
scholars, artists and craftsmen who will make speeches, hold
seminars, play hosts for visitors and give artistic performances
during the festival.
</P>
<P>
Many show-items, representative of the country's cultural and
historical features, including a set of 2,400-year-old chime
bells, ceramics, paintings, sculptures and a miniature Peking
Opera theater, are on display.
</P>
<P>
Some government ministries are exhibiting the examples of
social, economic, scientific, technological, educational and
cultural achievements made by China in the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai and Beijing municipal governments are displaying
the models of modernization planning for their cities, including
the development of Shanghai Pudong New Area and the renovation
plan for the ancient city of Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
