<HEADLINE> Hamas Claims Responsibility for Killing Israelis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Ezz-Eddin El-Kassam, the armed
wing of the Palestinian resistance movement Hamas, claimed
responsibility Wednesday for killing two Israeli settlers on
Monday near the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here Wednesday, Ezz-Eddin El-Kassam
battalions said one of their "volunteers" killed two Israeli
settlers on Monday in Meguido "as part of the struggle against the
Israeli occupation and settlers."
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Israeli police found the bodies of a 26-year-old man
and his wife, 21, in Meguido near Al-Afoula town in north Israel.
</P>
<P>
"The scores of arrests made recently by Palestinian security
forces against Hamas followers in Gaza will lead us to continue
our struggle till the end," the statement of Hamas armed wing said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian police arrested about 100 Hamas members in the past
two weeks after the armed Islamic organization threatened to
attack Israeli targets.
</P>
<P>
Hamas is opposed to making peace with Israel before Israel
withdraws from all occupied Palestinian territories. Hamas' armed
wing launched several attacks against Israel in the last few
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
