<HEADLINE> Uganda Transforming to Commercial Agriculture: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is transforming its
agricultural system in the east African country from subsistence
to commerce, Minister of Agriculture Kisamba Mugerwa said here
Wednesday
</P>
<P>
The minister revealed this while opening a three-day
international scientific conference organized by the Uganda
Veterinary Association.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture is streamlining veterinary services
in the country within the current legal framework and called for
the establishment of a veterinary board here, said Mugerwa.
</P>
<P>
He also called for more discussion of problems facing the
veterinary community in the country.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, a veterinary medicine expert with Makerere University
said that the faculty of veterinary medicine of the university is
soon completing an exercise intended to review the faculty
curriculum to suit new trends in the distribution of health
services for animals.
</P>
<P>
Makerere University is a co-organizer of the conference which
focused on the theme of improved animal health and population for
better quality of life. 
</P>
