<HEADLINE> Iran Seizes 114 Tons of Drugs in Five Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-one people lost their
lives in combating drug trafficking over the past five months,
during which 114 tons of different types of narcotics were seized
across Iran.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by an official with Iran's anti-drug
campaign headquarters on Wednesday. The official, who was
identified only as Serami, said the drugs were seized by
military, security and law enforcement forces.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the sidelines of the first workshop on useful
conduct to prevent youth from addiction, Serami said the drug
haul included six tons of heroin and morphine on transit to
Europe.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Islamic Republic News Agency, 61
people were martyred during clashes with drug smugglers since the
beginning of the Iranian year starting on March 21. So far, a
total of 2,700 people have lost their lives in anti-drug
operations.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the harsh anti-drug campaign, Iran has launched
a cultural campaign to teach people to keep away from
drugs. Serami called for all-out efforts in this regard by
families and all relevant organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
