<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0021 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Productive Offshore Oil Field Discovered in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Esso Exploration Angola Limited
(Esso) has announced an exciting discovery of productive oil
structure "Xilomba" in the Atlantic Ocean off the coast of Angola.
</P>
<P>
"Xilomba" is the sixth productive oil structure discovered in
the same block of sea called "Block 15" since 1998, by the Esso,
an affiliated company of the U.S. Exxon Corporation, mass media
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The newly-sunken oil well, denominated as "Xilomba-1" by Esso
and Sonangol, Angola's largest and sole petroleum company, is
situated in "Block 15", about 400 kilometers northwest to Luanda,
capital of Angola.
</P>
<P>
The "Xilomba-1" oil well, with a total depth of 2,876 meters,
passes 1, 335 meters through water before reaching the surface of
the earth crust.
</P>
<P>
According to Sonangol, which monopolizes the country's oil
industry, Xilomba-1 is "good for petroliferous reserve", with a
1,435-barrel-per-day volume of flow in a test of production.
</P>
<P>
Complete and exact evaluation of the productive capacity of the
oil field needs more biological studies, said the press.
</P>
<P>
In the same block of sea, five productive oil wells have been
announced since 1998, including wells named as Hungo, Kissanje,
Marimba, Dikanza and Chocalho.
</P>
<P>
Contractors of the Block 15 include Esso (having 40 percent of
the investment in the block), BP Exploration Angola Limited (26.67
percent), the Agip Angola Limited (20 percent) and the Den Norske
Stats Oljeselskap (13.33 percent), with Esso as the operator.
</P>
<P>
Angola, the second largest oil producing country in sub-Saharan
Africa, only after Nigeria, divided its seas, abundant of oil,
into blocks.
</P>
<P>
International companies have to compete with each other for the
 authorization of exploration by the government.
</P>
<P>
Sonangol, as the representative of the Angolan government in
the field, enjoys a share in the oil production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
