Islamic militants in Daghestan.
</P>
<P>
"The General Headquarters may also participate in planning an
operation for the eradication of militants in Kyrgyzstan," the
officers said.
</P>
<P>
Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev, who is currently in
Tashkent, Uzbekistan, plans to discuss joint steps in providing
assistance to Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan and Russia have both expressed the readiness to help
Kyrgyzstan. Tajikistan has also declared that it would get
involved. 
