<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 1 (Xinhua) - A small plane with 12 people on
board crashed in northern Tanzania on Wednesday morning and it is
still unclear if there were any survivors.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. embassy spokesman in Nairobi confirmed that 10 American
tourists, including six men and four women, were on board the
Cessna plane along with a Tanzanian tour guide and a pilot whose
nationality he did not know.
</P>
