<HEADLINE> Hombach: Balkan Stability Pact Can't Do Magic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting European Union (EU)
coordinator for the Balkan stability pact, Bodo Hombach, Wednesday
said in the northern Greek city of Thessaloniki that the Balkan
stability pact could not do magic.
</P>
<P>
Hombach, who arrived in Thessaloniki Wednesday and accompanied
by Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou, described the process
of the reconstructing the Balkans as a "marathon" and urged all
parties to be patient, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
"Patience and care are needed. We must not cultivate
expectations which can not subsequently be realized. We are at the
start of a marathon and I must stress that the stability pact can
not do magic," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hombach praised the city's role in implementing the Balkan
stability pact and hailed it as the perfect springboard for his
visits and activities in the region.
</P>
<P>
The EU leaders have decided late June to base its agency for
the Balkan reconstruction in Thessaloniki, the largest city in
northern Greece. 
</P>
