<HEADLINE> Iranian Army Kills 7 Drug-Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Seven smugglers and armed
bandits have been killed by Iranian Army's anti-smuggling special
force in eastern borders.
</P>
<P>
The official Islamic Republic News Agency quoted an army
brigadier general as saying Wednesday that the armed bandits were
Afghan nationals who were crossing the border with a large caravan
of narcotics.
</P>
<P>
The army also seized a large amount of ammunition from the
traffickers, he added.
</P>
<P>
Iran has been a key transit route for drug trafficking from
Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe and oil-rich Gulf Arab
countries. Over the past two days, about 1,030 kilograms of
narcotics were reportedly seized in the eastern province of
Khorasan bordering Afghanistan. 
