<HEADLINE> URGENT: China Culture Week Opens in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The China Culture Week -`99
Paris was formally opened Wednesday evening by Ding Guangen, a
member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and Minister of Publicity, and Frederico Mayor, Secretary
General of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural
Organizations (UNESCO).
</P>
<P>
Attending the opening ceremony were Catherine Trautmann, French
Minister of Culture and Communications, and Zhao Qizheng, director
of Information Office of the State Council of China.
</P>
<P>
The China Culture Week - `99 Paris will be held until September
12, during which an exhibition on Chinese ancient and modern
culture and on the social and economic development of the country
will be open to the public at the UNESCO Building in central
Paris.
</P>
<P>
The event is jointly held by China and UNESCO to celebrate the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of
China. 
</P>
