<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Founders of Congolese Rebel Group Satisfied with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The majority founders of the
Rally for Congolese Democracy (RCD) have expressed satisfaction
that Congo will now be reconstructed according to the will of the
Congolese after the peace accord was signed Tuesday in Lusaka by
46 founder members of the major rebel group.
</P>
<P>
Chief of rural development department based in Goma in eastern
part of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), Getrude
Kitembo, said here Wednesday that the first thing was to have
democratic elections where leaders would be elected.
</P>
<P>
Kitembo said the regime of President Laurent Kabila was imposed
on the people, but with the spirit shown at the signing of the
cease-fire pact, there would be leadership elected by the people.
</P>
<P>
She said voting was a sign of democratization and not something
imposed by others but people should choose what they want.
</P>
<P>
"If everything goes according to plan, we should have a new
leadership in the DRC in two months time," she said.
</P>
<P>
And permanent secretary of founders Mamba college of the RCD,
Nkolo Balamage said that the signing of the cease-fire pact would
have a positive bearing to opposition parties that were operating
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Balamage said the RCD had been talking to Etiene Tsisekedi, who
had a large following in the country on what role he could play in
the new government.
</P>
<P>
He said that everybody in the Congo was looking not only for
peace but democracy to prevail in the country after years of
chaos.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that his party was compelled to use force because
Kabila did not want to change and this was the same view shared by
Tsisekedi.
</P>
<P>
"Tsisekedi has a role to play in the new government. .We want a
national government in which all forces of the Congo are found,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He further emphasized that in future there is need for Great
Lakes regions to offer protection to each other for the sake of
security in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
