<HEADLINE> Second Stage of Sino-Yemeni Friendship Flyover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni Vice-President Abdo Rabo
Mansour Hadi launched on Wednesday the second stage of the
Sino-Yemeni Friendship Flyover in downtown Sanaa.
</P>
<P>
After laying the foundation stone of the second and last stage
of the flyover, Hadi inspected the construction site of the
project, which costs up to 6 million U.S. dollars contributed by
China.
</P>
<P>
The four-lane flyover is five meters high and 402 meters long
with a middle circle whose diameter is 15.05 meters.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the flyover, designed by China, was started
in mid March and was expected to be completed in May, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Hadi hailed at the ceremony the smooth development of the
friendly ties between Yemen and China.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was also attended by Yemeni Minister of
Construction, Housing and Urban Planning Abdullah Hussein Al-Dafee
and Chinese Ambassador to Yemen Shi Yanchun. 
</P>
