- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Ezz-Eddin El-Kassam, the armed wing of the Palestinian
resistance movement Hamas, claimed responsibility Wednesday for
killing two Israeli settlers on Monday near the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here Wednesday, Ezz-Eddin El-Kassam
battalions said one of their "volunteers" killed two Israeli
settlers on Monday in Meguido "as part of the struggle against the
Israeli occupation and settlers."
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Israeli police found the bodies of a 26-year-old man
and his wife, 21, in Meguido near Al-Afoula town in north Israel.
(BC-Hamas-Israeli Settlers-Killing) 
</P>
</TEXT>
