<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meningitis Epidemic Infects 4,000 in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 4,000 people are
suffering from a meningitis epidemic that broke out in early June
in the northeastern county of Iasi, Romania.
</P>
<P>
4,127 people, most under the age of 19, were reported to be
infected, according to a Health Ministry warning reported on local
media Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Most infections of the acute meningitis, which have been
clinically confirmed, have been found to be situated in the
northern and northeastern part of the country, such as Iasi, Neamt,
Botosani, Suceava and Bacau. No meningitis linked deaths have yet
been reported.
</P>
<P>
A similar epidemic in 1973 was contained only after a large
part of the population received immunization, said local
epidemiologists. They also said that epidemics similar to the one
occurring in Romania now were, in the past nine years, reported in
South Korea, Canada, Switzerland, Cuba, Poland, Spain, Australia,
Norway and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry warned that measures to prevent the
epidemic from spreading were still in force and recommended that
people wash fruit and vegetables thoroughly, wash their hands
before eating, and avoid contact with flies and mosquitoes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Calls for Halt to Violence in East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Britain expressed its "deep
concern" over the wave of violence in East Timor on Thursday and
said the random violence must stop.
</P>
<P>
"I am deeply distressed by the violence that we have seen in
East Timor since the ballot," said Foreign Secretary Robin Cook in
a statement issued by the foreign office.
</P>
<P>
"There can be no possible excuse, and no purpose, to the random
violence that we have seen in the last few days. It must stop," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Violence has spread in East Timor this week after people in
that former Portuguese colony voted in a United Nation's-run
ballot. The ballot is expected to show huge support for
independence from Indonesia's 23-year-long rule.
</P>
<P>
"We look forward to the result of that ballot when it is
announced," Cook said.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, pro-Jakarta militia went on the rampage near the
United Nations headquarters in Dili, the capital city of East
Timor, killing at least five people, one of them hacked to death
with machetes in front of television cameras.
</P>
<P>
"The prime responsibility for halting that violence rests with
the government of Indonesia. It is very important that their
security forces should now bring order to the streets of East
Timor and halt those who are carrying out the intimidation," Cook
said.
</P>
<P>
"I will be communicating to my colleague, the foreign minister
of Indonesia, our concern at the reports of that violence and of
the intimidation of the people of East Timor," the statement said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
