<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, September 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA -- The Conference on Disarmament (CD), as a multilateral
disarmament negotiating body, is irreplaceable in terms of its
status and role, the Chinese ambassador for disarmament affairs,
Li Changhe, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Even though it has not been able to get down to treaty
negotiations for the time being, the conference can still function
as an important forum where dialogue can be conducted on major
issues of international peace and security, and on some specific
disarmament items," Li said at a CD plenary. (China-Disarmament)
</P>
