<HEADLINE> Silver, Gold Prices Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Both Silver and gold prices
turned weak Thursday on the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay)
following fresh price falls in the global market.
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) ended lower at 8,020 rupees
(186.51 U.S. dollars) per kilogram from the last close of 8,075
rupees (187.79 dollars), showing a fresh fall of 55 rupees (1.28
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) fell by 50 rupees (1.04 dollars) to
end at 7,905 rupees (183.84 dollars) per kilogram from the last
close of 7,950 rupees (184.88 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, standard gold fell by 10 rupees (0.23 dollars) to
end at 4,050 rupees (94.19 dollars) for 10 grams from the last
close of 4,060 rupees (94.42 dollars). 
