<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roman Catholic Priest Killed in Eastern India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- In yet another attack on
Christian missionary, a Roman Catholic priest was killed and
another injured by unknown assailants early Thursday in eastern
Indian, reports reaching here said,
</P>
<P>
The priest, Aruldoss, was attacked by a gang armed with bows
and arrows in the early morning hours in a village named Jamabani
belonging to Mayurbhanj district of Orissa, according to the Press
Trust of India (PTI).
</P>
<P>
Neither the identity of the attackers nor the motive behind the
killing was immediately known.
</P>
<P>
This is the second such attack on missionaries after the
gruesome murder of Graham Staines and his two sons from Australia
on January 22 this year in the same district of the state.
</P>
<P>
Indian caretaker Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee Thursday
strongly condemned the killing of Aruldoss and asked the state
government to "show its efficiency" by arresting the culprits.
</P>
<P>
"I strongly condemn the dastardly killing of the Christian
priest and especially urge the government of Orissa to show its
efficiency and capability in quickly arresting the culprits in
this and previous such crimes," Vajpayee said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
While expressing condolences to the family of the deceased,
Vajpayee said, "It is extremely distressing that such murderous
attacks on representatives of a minority community should be
taking place unchecked and with alarming regularity in Orissa."
</P>
<P>
The incident came close on the heels of the killing of a Muslim
trader Sheikh Rehman in the area on August 26.
</P>
<P>
Ironically, the incident occurred barely a few hours after the
ruling Congress and several other political parties of the state
held a state-wide rally to protest against the continuing attacks
on the minorities.
</P>
<P>
Like the previous incidents, the latest killing occurred on the
day of a Hindu festival, Janmasthami. The Australian missionary
was killed on the day of Saraswati Puja while Rehman was hacked to
death on Raksha Bandhan.
</P>
<P>
No arrest had been made so far in connection with the
incidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Pledges Partnership With Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 2 (Xinhua) -- President Boris Yeltsin said
Thursday that Russia will continue to maintain a friendship and
strategic partnership with Moldova.
</P>
<P>
"We want to live in peace, friendship, and develop a more
strategic partnership with a united Moldova," Yeltsin told
visiting Moldovan President Petru Lucinschi in the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
President Yeltsin praised the productive and constructive
atmosphere of the talks. "For those issues that have accumulated
between us, not a single one remains unresolved or unsatisfied,"
the Interfax news agency quoted Yeltsin as saying.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents signed a treaty encouraging economic
cooperation through 2008.
</P>
<P>
According to Yeltsin's Deputy Chief of Staff Sergei Prikhodko,
the two leaders addressed bilateral issues and the Transdnestr
settlement.
</P>
<P>
"These talks demonstrate that both Moscow and Chisinau
appreciate the trend toward stabilization in Transdnestr. There is
no more bloodshed in that region and negotiations have been
directed to the appropriate political channels. The prospects for
a Transdnestr settlement are encouraging," Prikhodko said.
</P>
<P>
Fighting erupted in March 1992 in the Transdnestr region
between Moldovan security forces and Slavic separatists who feared
Moldova would merge with neighboring Romania.
</P>
<P>
In a plebiscite on March 6, 1994, voters in Moldova supported
independence, rather than unification with Romania. Defying the
Moldovan government, voters in the breakaway Dnestr region held
legislative elections and approved a separatist constitution on
December 24, 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
