<HEADLINE> Russian Population Down 406,200 in First Half of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The population of Russia
decreased by 0.28 percent, or 406,200 persons in the first half of
this year. As of July 1, the population of the country was 145.9
million, the State Statistics Agency said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period last year, the decline in the
population nearly doubled.
</P>
<P>
From January to June in 1998, the population of Russia
diminished by 226,700, or 0.15 percent, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The declining population was attributed to a rising death rate
as well as a decrease in migration from outside Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
