<HEADLINE> Party School Opens Computer-aided Distance Learning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua)-- Arming itself with the latest
technology to educate its cadres, the Communist Party of China (
CPC) recently completed a computer-aided network that links the
Party School in Beijing with five local Party schools.
</P>
<P>
The five schools are in Shandong, Hainan and Sichuan provinces
and the municipalities of Chongqing and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Party School and the local Party schools will be able to
share their teaching resources as well as "campus news" via the
computer-aided distance learning program.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and president of the Party
School, attended the opening ceremony for the launching of the
computerized network on Wednesday. He said he hopes the network
will be a model for party schools throughout the country.
</P>
