<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Accuses Eritrea of Mounting Border Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian troops Thursday
repelled an offensive by the Eritrean troops at Chin Keren on the
Zalambessa front, the Office of the Ethiopian Government
Spokesperson said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean attack continued through Wednesday night and ended
Thursday morning at 6:00 a.m. local time, it said.
</P>
<P>
Zalambessa, a border town of Ethiopia, is situated in the mid
way of the 1,000 km-long Ethio-Eritrean war front.
</P>
<P>
There is no immediate comment from the Eritrean side on the
alleged attack.
</P>
<P>
The Zalambessa constituency consists of 150,000 people.
Ethiopia accused Eritrean of occupying the town and the
surrounding districts of Hadish Alem, Hadish Tesfa, Martha and
Sobia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
