<HEADLINE> Senior Official Stresses Qualification of Government Functionaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor and
secretary-general of the State Council Wang Zhongyu today urged
government employees to be more motivated to become better
qualified.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who is also the president of the State Administrative
College, made the call at the college's fall semester opening
ceremony. He noted that all government functionaries must be
politically qualified and that they should bear in mind their
basic duty of serving the people.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, government officials should follow the law as
they carry out their work, as China is strengthening its rule of
law, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the officials in various departments must be
specialists in their own fields and learn better management skills,
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
