<HEADLINE> Compaq Promotes 8-way Servers in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua)-- The Compaq company, one of the
world's computer giants, today made available here two kinds of 8-
way servers which can operate eight CPUs of Pentium III at the
same time.
</P>
<P>
The servers, named Proliant 8000 and Proliant 8500 are run
under a multiprocessing system called Profusion, which was jointly
developed by Compaq and Intel.
</P>
<P>
They support several kinds of operating systems, such as
Windows NT and Windows 2000, according to James Lien, Compaq's
product marketing director.
</P>
<P>
Lien said that as the first producer of 8-way servers, Compaq
has seen great potential in the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Chinese internet service providers will be able to offer more
services with Proliant 8000 and 8500, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
