<HEADLINE> Sensex Slightly Down in Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (Sensex)
dropped 94.71 points Thursday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE)
following sustained profit-taking and bull liquidation.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index opened lower at 4,813.73 and
dropped further to post a low of 4,720.19 before closing at
4,729.73 as against Wednesday's close of 4,824.44, netting a loss
of 94.71 points or 1.96 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index dropped 43.01 points to 2,110.23 from the
last close of 2,153.24.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted remarkably down at
484.44 and 185.33 compared with the last close of 494.85 and
189.53 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index also registered a sharp fall of 30.45 points
to close at 1,430.93 as against Wednesday's close of 1,461.38.
</P>
