<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Following are today's
diplomatic news highlights:
</P>
<P>
 Chinese President Leaves to Visit Asia-Pacific Countries
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin left here today to start a state
visit to Thailand, Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
He will also attend the 7th Informal Leadership Meeting of the
Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) to be held in Auckland,
New Zealand on September 12-13.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice-Premier Meets ADB Delegation
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met with a delegation from
Board of Directors of Asian Development Bank (ADB) here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed the visitors on China's economic restructuring,
active fiscal policy and economic developments. He said that China
is ready to continue its cooperation with ADB.
</P>
<P>
 Foreign Leaders Not Being Invited to China's National Day
Celebration
</P>
<P>
China says it will not invite foreign heads of state and
government to activities marking the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China, the Foreign Ministry
has announced.
</P>
<P>
The decision is in keeping with Chinese government regulations,
Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi told a routine press conference here
today, at the end of the six-week summer holiday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
