<HEADLINE> 30 Feared Drowned in Indian Boat Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Some 30 persons were feared
drowned Thursday when a country boat capsized in a tributary of
the turbulent Burhi Gandak in Muzaffarpur District of Bihar, local
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The boat, carrying more than 50 passengers, was caught in a
whirlpool and sank while sailing to Kolhua-Bagamber village from
Mithansarai Thursday morning, the Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
While 20 persons swam to safety, 30 others were reported to
have been drowned, a local official said.
</P>
<P>
Eight bodies had so far been recovered while an intense search
continued to locate the missing passengers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
