<HEADLINE> Business Partner City Members Meet in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of Business
Partner City (BPC) gathered here today to share their views on
economic issues in the wake of the Asian financial crisis as well
as future cooperation between the member cities.
</P>
<P>
The participants said there should be more exchanges in
personnel and information technology, and cooperation should be
expanded in food, pharmaceutical and environmental industries.
</P>
<P>
They also decided that Melbourne, Australia, which is a new
member city, will host the next BPC roundtable meeting.
</P>
<P>
BPC was formed in 1988, launched by Osaka, Japan, and now has
12 member cities. Shanghai joined the Asian-Oceanic organization
in 1995.  
