<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola Urges to Bring Assassins of Journalists to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan Ministry of Social
Communication urged that the assassins of two journalists of the
National Radio of Angola should be taken to court, mass media
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement Wednesday that it was shocked
by the death of Mauricio Francisco Cristovao, a journalist of
"Radio 5", the sports channel of the National Radio of Angola, and
Joao Adriano da Costa, staff member of the same radio station.
</P>
<P>
The assassinations occurred on August 31 in "different places
and under different circumstances, according to the police," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the crimes were committed at dawn in the streets
by armed bandits, which pullulate rapidly recently in Luanda,
capital of Angola.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also expressed its condolence to the families of
the victims over the death of the journalists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
