<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan, Armenia Sign Treaty of Friendship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev signed a treaty of friendship and cooperation on
Thursday with visiting Armenian President Robert Kocharyan. The
agreement is intended to boost the traditionally friendly ties
shared between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Interfax news agency said that in addition to the treaty, the
two presidents also agreed to establish a joint economic and trade
commission.
</P>
<P>
At the press conference, the two presidents spoke with deep
appreciation for the traditional ties of friendship and mutual
trust shared between them.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev said his country is hopeful that Armenia will
resolve the issues relevant to the Nagorno-Karabakh area, which is
in Azerbaijan and whose population is mainly ethnic Armenians.
</P>
<P>
The Armenian president arrived here Wednesday for a two-day
visit. During his stay, the two countries also signed agreements
on trade, aviation and customs.  
