<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Visitors to Horti-Expo Exceed 6 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The exposition has been underway since May 1 in Kunming,
capital of Yunnan Province, in southwest China. August witnessed
the largest arrival of visitors, at a daily average of over 50,000.
</P>
<P>
Over 90 countries and international organizations have opened
gardens or pavilions in the exhibition area that covers more than
200 ha..
</P>
<P>
It is the first major international exposition organized by
China, and it is also the last large international event to be
sponsored by the Chinese government this century.
</P>
<P>
Closing day for the gala is October 31. Both central and local
governments hope it will be a good opportunity for Yunnan to
develop its tourism industry. 
</P>
