<HEADLINE> Angola, Congos Discuss Situation Along Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Official Journal de Angola newspaper reported that during the
meeting held in RC capital Brazzaville, the ministers will still
have an examination on the political-military situation in the
three countries.
</P>
<P>
According to a source close to the Angolan delegation, the
three-day Brazzaville meeting to be ended Friday will establish
various mixed commissions responsible for watching over the
fulfillment of all the decisions made in previous meetings among
the three countries.
</P>
<P>
During the latest tripartite conference held in Democratic
Congo capital Kinshasa this May, the countries decided to create
practical mechanisms for combatting the armed groups which engaged
in subversive activities in the three countries.
</P>
<P>
Angola has common frontier with Congo Brazzaville and Congo
Kinshasa in the northwest enclave province of Cabinda, and has
about 2,000 kilometers of common frontier with Democratic Congo to
the north and northeast. 
</P>
