<HEADLINE> Ride Collapse Sends 16 Toronto Children to Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- As many as 16 children were
sent to hospital Wednesday night after the collapse of a spinning
ride at an amusement park in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Local television said Thursday that the abrupt halt of the "
wave swinger" ride in the midair caused neck and back injuries to
the kids aged between five to 15.
</P>
<P>
Ambulances were immediately called in to rescue the injured
children off the swing ride. Nearly 50 people were on board at the
time of the accident resulted from a mechanical failure, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Mechanics are conducting an overall examination at the
amusement park to ensure there won't be any more scare causing "
shakeups",according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
