<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Visitors in Tour Groups to Macao Soar in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of visitors in tour
groups to Macao was 87,278 in July, up 23.9 percent over the same
month of 1998, the latest official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to the figures released Thursday by the Macao Census
and Statistics Department, those coming from China's mainland
areas and Taiwan accounted for 84.8 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Visitors to Macao in tour groups in the first seven months of
the year were 595,743, an increase of 19.4 percent over the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, 9,283 Macao residents, out of a population
of some 430,000, traveled to other places in tour groups in July,
a decrease of 10.7 percent from the same month of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The most favored destinations of tour for Macao residents were
China's mainland areas (56.9 percent), Thailand (8.2 percent) and
Taiwan region (7.3 percent).
</P>
<P>
However, the number of Macao residents traveled to other places
in tour groups between January and July this year increased 13.9
percent over the same period of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
