<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on China-Thailand Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The China-Thailand relations
have become a good example of amiable coexistence and friendly
cooperation between countries with different social systems,
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in the Thai capital Thursday afternoon to begin a
five-day state visit at the invitation of Thai King Bhumibol
Adulyadej.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement upon arrival, Jiang said, "China and
Thailand are close and friendly neighbors. The traditional
friendship between our two peoples goes back to ancient times,"
</P>
<P>
He noted that since the establishment of diplomatic ties 24
years ago, with the concerted efforts of both sides, the mutually
beneficial cooperation between the two countries in various fields
has made considerable progress.
</P>
<P>
In the spirit of breaking new ground for the future, Jiang went
on to say, "I am ready to work with the Thai side to promote the
all-dimensional friendly relations and cooperation between China
and Thailand in an even healthier and still more stable direction,
so as to bring benefit to our two peoples."
</P>
<P>
"I am sure this wish of mine will be realized," Jiang said,
adding he is "very pleased to come to Thailand for a state visit,
bringing the friendly sentiments of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
During his visit in Bangkok, Jiang is expected to hold separate
meetings with the king, President of the National Assembly Wan
Muhammad Nor Matha, President of the Supreme Court Pintip
Sucharitkul, Prime Minister Chuan, and Privy Councilor and former
prime minister Prem Tinsulanonda.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow, he will also deliver a speech on Sino-Thai relations
and China's policy towards Southeast Asia at the Thailand Cultural
Center. 
</P>
