<HEADLINE> NBA Legend Magic Johnson to Play for Swedish Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 2 (Xinhua) - Former NBA star Magic Johnson
will play for the MagicM7 of the Swedish basketball league late
next month, according to sports reports here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who won Olympic gold and five NBA championships with
the Los Angeles Lakers, is to play the starting point guard for
the MagicM7 against Sallen from Uppsala in his first game on
October 26.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to visiting Sweden and playing with my team,not
just one or two games," Johnson told Reuters.
</P>
<P>
"To play several games with my team is part of a process to
educate the players. They are learning during practice but for me
to show what I mean, we really have to play together."
</P>
<P>
MagicM7 changed its name from M7Boras after they made the
agreement with Johnson. Last year M7Boras finished fifth in the
Swedish league and missed the play-off.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, 40, said he picked the Swedish league because he was
impressed by the interest in basketball when he was here for an
exhibition team event in 1996.
</P>
<P>
For the last three years, Johnson has turned his hand to
business, with his company, Magic Johnson Enterprise, branching
into cinemas, a record company and a basketball camp.
</P>
<P>
Johnson tested HIV-positive in 1991. He retired at the start of
the 1991-92 season but made a brief comeback, playing for the
United States "Dream Team" who won gold at the 1992 Barcelona
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Johnson returned to the game again in January 1996 and played
half of the season but when the Lakers were eliminated from the
playoffs, Johnson retired for good from the NBA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
