<HEADLINE> South Korean Women Archers Set New Asian Team Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- South Korean women archers on
Thursday set the new Asian record for FITA round team record in
the qualification round at the Asian Archery Championships here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ha Na Young, Lee Hee Jung and Kim Du Ri combined to score 4,069
points to improve the previous record by 16 points. The previous
mark was set by another South Korean team in October last year in
Bangkok, Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Archery Federation only considers the best results in
Asian level competition for the Asian record although the South
Koreans have claimed many world records.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans, all second string archers except Ha, filled
the top four places in the qualification round. Ha led with 1,361
points, followed by Hee at 1,355, Kim at 1,353 and Kang Hyun Ji at
1,349.
</P>
<P>
The rankings in the qualification round will decide the
fixtures of the elimination round slated for early Friday. The
medalists for women's individual will be decided on Friday
afternoon while the women's team title on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
