this month. The ruling Taliban, who control nearly 90 percent of
the country's territory including the capital Kabul, have been
demanding international recognition since they overran Kabul three
years ago.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations still recognizes the deposed President
Burhanuddin Rabbani as the legitimate Afghan ruler. Pakistan,
Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates are the only three
states which recognize the Taliban government.
</P>
<P>
Anwari said the meeting, chaired by Commander Ahmad Shah
Masood, also reviewed military matters and decided to open new
fronts against the Taliban. 
