<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese Foreign Minister
Mustafa Osman Ismail has admitted that his country's ties with
Egypt have not returned to normal, but he stressed they are in a
better shape.
</P>
<P>
He added that Egypt has come to realize the U.S. attempt to
divide and destabilize Sudan, the Sudanese official daily Al Anbaa
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ismail said that his government accepts the Egyptian-Libyan
initiative to hold a national dialog aimed at achieving a national
reconciliation and agrees to attend a discussion of a preparatory
committee at any time and anywhere.
</P>
<P>
