any topics, adding that realization of national reconciliation
will expand the government's achievements.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old civil war between Sudanese government and the
southern rebels, and the ensuing famine have claimed over 1.5
million lives in the poor African country.
</P>
<P>
Ties between Sudan and Egypt plummeted in 1995 after an
unsuccessful attack on Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in
Ethiopia. Egypt accused Sudan of harboring the attackers, an
accusation denied by Khartoum.
</P>
<P>
The two countries began to improve relations since last
year. As a goodwill overture, Sudan returned part of the Egyptian
property it seized over chilling relations after an
Islamist-backed government assumed power in 1989. 
</P>
