next May, according to a source at the municipal water resources
bureau. The swimming areas will be able to accommodate more than
30,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Complaints by the people of Beijing during this summer's
intense heat, when more than 20,000 people went for a dip in lakes
and rivers every day and caused water pollution and other problems,
led to the decision.
</P>
<P>
The swimming areas will be located alongside an aqueduct from
Miyun County to the urban areas and in the southern part of the
city.  
