<HEADLINE> Int'l Meeting on Animal Reproduction Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The 6th International
Conference on Biotechnology in Animal Production opened here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference, being held for the first time in
Nepal, will focus on issues related to the recent achievements in
biotechnology in animal reproduction, i.e. embryo transfer, frozen
semen for cattle and buffalo and the cloning technique of animals.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 participants including professors, scientific
researchers in animal reproduction and cattle farmers from Japan,
the United States, Canada, China, Indonesia, India and Egypt are
attending the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The conference is organized by the Department of Livestock
Services of Nepal, Nepal Agriculture Research Council and
Yamaguchi University of Japan among others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
