<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Indonesia to Strengthen Border Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian and
Indonesian military forces will build a joint border post at
Timbang Mangaris, Sabah, East Malaysia, to enhance security along
their common border in Borneo.
</P>
<P>
The border post would be ready by August next year, Commander
of the First Malaysian Infantry Division Major-General Pahlawan
Mohamed Azumi Mohamad said Thursday at a news conference in
Kuching, Sarawak, East Malaysia, after holding talks with
Major-General Zainuri Hashim, the military area commander for
Kalimantan, Indonesia, who is on a visit to Sarawak.
</P>
<P>
"Apart from ensuring security, the post will also strengthen
friendship between the two military forces," Bernama news agency
quoted Mohamed Azumi said.
</P>
<P>
The joint border post will be the third along the
Malaysian-Indonesian border. At present, there are two such common
border posts in Sarawak.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Indonesian commander said at the joint press
conference that the Indonesian and Malaysian Armed Forces have
excellent relations and many border problems have been amicably
resolved between them.
</P>
<P>
This relationship would be maintained through more exchanges of
information and joint exercises, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
