<HEADLINE> Volume of Hong Kong's Re-exports Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's re-
exports in June 1999 rose by 0.2 percent over the same month last
year and that of domestic exports fell by 11.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release by the Hong Kong SAR Census and
Statistics Department reaching here on Thursday, in June the
volume of Hong Kong's total exports dropped by 1.5 percent while
its volume of imports lost by 2.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing with the same period last year, Hong Kong's volume of
re-exports in the first six months of 1999 decreased by 2.1
percent and its volume of domestic exports by 11.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
The department said that the change in volume of trade is
derived from the change in trade value with the effect of price
changes discounted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
