<HEADLINE> Relations Between Zambia and Angola Normalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A delegation from Angola will
soon be in Zambia on re-affirming relations between the two
countries, Zambian government has disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Foreign Minister Keli Walubita was quoted by Thursday's
 newspapers as saying that his Angolan counterpart, Joao Bernado
de Miranda, would lead a delegation to Zambia before a reciprocal
visit to Luanda was undertaken.
</P>
<P>
Walubita said the tension that had existed between Zambia and
Angola had subsided, the visits would be undertaken in the spirit
of an agreement reached at the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
summit in Algiers on July 13, 1999 when the two ministers met.
</P>
<P>
Angola has been alleging that it had credible information
confirming substantial involvement of the Zambian authorities in
the logistical and military support to the National Union for the
Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) to enable the rebel movement
perpetuate the war in that country. But Zambia denied the
allegation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
