evident when the president signed and endorsed the master plan
document on April 24, 1997.
</P>
<P>
"The master plan of controlling illicit drug trafficking and
abuse is a reflection of the government's desire to promote good
health in this country," he said.
</P>
<P>
Research results on the extent of drug abuse and trafficking
are expected to reveal information to be used to identify
deficiencies of the current prevention programs and would also
offer a base for evaluation, He added. 
