<HEADLINE> Basri International Folk Arts Festival Opens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The 15th International Folk
Arts Festival opened Wednesday night at the Basri fortress, some
145 kilometers south of the capital city of Damascus.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony attended by Syrian Culture
Minister Nagah Al Attar, festival manager Ass'ad Fadda said the
event provides an opportunity for the demonstration of Arab and
international arts and exchange among different art schools.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, which takes place every two years, a
series of art-related events including flower displays, folk
fashion show, exhibitions of native handicrafts of the southern
Syrian governorate of Deraa will be held.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one foreign troupes, including 10 Arab ones, will also
perform their works at the Basri theater.
</P>
<P>
The small city of Basir is famous for a Roman theater that
dates back to the second century A.D..
</P>
<P>
The 45-meter-long and eight-meter-deep theater can accommodate
15,000 spectators and is considered the best and most beautiful
Roman theater at that time. 
</P>
