<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Maids to Destroy Families in UAE: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The large number of foreign
maids in the United Arab Emirates (UAE) is a "time-bomb" to
destroy the base of traditional families and hurt the future
generation, a senior police official has warned.
</P>
<P>
The fact that many women in UAE have given up their household
responsibilities and housemaids are bringing up children has
resulted in break-up of many families, said Lieutenant Ibrahim
Abdulla Al Hosani of the Abu Dhabi Police Criminal Evidence
Department.
</P>
<P>
In a report published recently by the Interior Ministry's Al
Shurta (Police) magazine, Hosani said undue employment of maids
and nannies is increasingly weakening the strong bond between
the mother and child especially.
</P>
<P>
"The situation is getting worse as the number of housemaids
and nannies from different beliefs and cultures is continuing to
grow," Hosani said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that unmarried housemaids account for 57
percent and the rest are minors. Many maids allegedly had
unlawful relationships with their employers which resulted in
break-up of the family.
</P>
<P>
"In this light of these facts and statistics, I believe
we are facing a serious problem which needs radical steps for
a solution," Hosani cautioned.
</P>
<P>
"Apparently, it is a gloomy future for the younger
generation which has grown up away from their parents' care
and affection. In fact, the maids' religion, language and
culture have such a strong influence on them that many of
them cannot speak Arabic," he said.
</P>
<P>
He called upon parents not to ignore their responsibility
of bringing up their children and urged everyone to work
toward protecting the young generation from the danger it faces
- the danger posed by housemaids.
</P>
<P>
"We should all wake up before it is too late," Hosani added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
