<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Swiss food group Nestle SA
has reached an agreement with a food company in China to acquire
80 percent of the latter's share capital, according to a Nestle
press release Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Nestle did not disclose the cost of the deal with the Totole
Group, the market leader in chicken bouillon in China. It said
that Totole's sales volume is around 40 million Swiss francs (
