<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Computer Hacker Jailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A 24 year old computer hacker
has been jailed for eighteen months in Guangzhou for destroying an
information network.
</P>
<P>
It is the first such case in south China's Guangdong Province
since the revised Criminal Law of 1997 stipulated that such
activities will be dealt with as crimes.
</P>
<P>
Lu Xuewen, a local resident with only senior high school
education, joined a domestic hackers organization in April 1997
and learned how to attack computer networks like Chinanet from the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
He was found guilty by the Guangzhou Intermediate People's
Court of using his personal laptop to attack the Guangzhou main
frame of Chinanet and Lantian BBS main frame with stolen account
numbers in January and February 1998, and starting up his own
account numbers in a bid to control the two systems over a long
term.
</P>
<P>
He was also guilty of rewriting the password into the
Guangzhou main frame three times, causing the system to crash for
15 hours.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
