<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in
Tokyo Thursday, with investors remaining reluctant to take clear
positions amid the yen's strength against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 171.23 points, or 0.96
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 17,631.25.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX) covering all
First Section issues, however, gained 0.75 point or 0.05 percent
to 1,496.99.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section edged down to 602.95 million
shares from Wednesday's 612.57 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Sakura Bank was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Traders said they expect overall trading to remain sluggish for
a while, as investors are likely to take a wait-and-see attitude
ahead of next Thursday's release of Japan's gross domestic product
(GDP) data for the April-June quarter.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented issues were weak, as the strong yen is likely
to hurt their earnings, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers far exceeded
gainers 871 to 372, with 92 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
<P>
On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the U.S. dollar briefly dipped
to the 108 yen level for the first time since January 12, but
later gained ground on short covering.
</P>
<P>
At 5 p.m. local time (0800 GMT), the U.S. currency was quoted
at 109.40-43 yen, up from 109.00-03 yen at 9 a.m.(0000 GMT), and
from 109.10-20 yen in New York overnight. It was traded at 109.21-
24 yen in Tokyo late Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
