<HEADLINE> Uganda's Radio, TV Merge News Rooms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Radio Uganda and Uganda
Television, both broadcasting departments owned by the central
government, have merged their news rooms in a restructuring
process.
</P>
<P>
The merger, which took effect this week, was confirmed by
Samuel Muwanguzi, news room editor of Radio Uganda.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Xinhua Thursday morning,
Muwanguzi said the merger is a move toward the creation of the
Uganda Broadcasting Agency for harmonizing operations of both
stations, maximizing resources and creating uniformity.
</P>
<P>
It would also improve on the morale and motivation of the
staff, he added.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has a plan to merge Radio Uganda, Uganda News Agency and
Uganda Television Station into a broadcasting agency. Most of the
working staff with the nearly defunct news agency had been
assigned to work for the radio and TV stations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
