<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Military Chief Denies Allowing Violence in East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Defense Forces
(TNI) Chief Gen. Wiranto Thursday said TNI and Indonesian Police
(Polri) had never let any kind of violence take place in East
Timor.
</P>
<P>
"TNI and Polri have never let it happen. We have missions to
prevent and neutralize any kind of violence," Wiranto told
reporters here before attending a meeting with the House of
Representatives' Commission I.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto, who is also minister of defense and security, said
security matter in East Timor was the responsibility of TNI and
Polri.
</P>
<P>
"(Foreign Minister Ali) Alatas has reiterated that Indonesia is
responsible for East Timor's security affairs," he said.
</P>
<P>
Responding to demands to have the presence of U.N. peacekeeping
force in East Timor, Wiranto said it was not easy to do that.
</P>
<P>
"There should be special reasons to bring up U.N. peacekeeping
force," he said, adding that the Indonesian government and its
security officers had had anticipation plans to face the worst
possible happening when the U.N.-sponsored direct ballot result is
announced.
</P>
<P>
He said news reports on the shooting incident at the U.N.
Mission in East Timor (UNAMET) Wednesday were exaggerated.
</P>
<P>
At least two people were reportedly killed in the latest
violence targeting at the UNAMET in Dili, capital of East Timor.
</P>
<P>
"I had been informed by UNAMET Chairman and U.N. Special Envoy
for East Timor Jamsheed Marker about the incident," he said,
noting that the press needs to clarify the reports.
</P>
<P>
He, however, acknowledged that there was small-scale clash
between pro-autonomy and pro-independence supporters in the
region.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 98.6 percent of some 450,000 eligible
voters in East Timor cast their ballots on August 30.
</P>
<P>
The direct ballot will determine whether East Timor, a former
Portuguese colony, will enjoy wide-ranging autonomy within
Indonesia or get independence. East Timor integrated into
Indonesia in 1976, but the move was never recognized by the United
Nations. 
</P>
