<HEADLINE> California Exports To Asia Show Signs Of Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 1 (Xinhua) -- California exports to Asia
in the second quarter showed the first clear signs of a broad
recovery, reflecting Asia's astonishing comeback.
</P>
<P>
South Korea was the first major export country to bounce back,
and California shipments there rose by 37 percent in the second
quarter, according to data released Tuesday by the Massachusetts
Institute for Social and Economic Research.
</P>
<P>
However, the one lingering weakness in Asia is Japan. Shipments
there fell by 12 percent in the second quarter after a decline of
10 percent in the first quarter and a drop of 16 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
In all, California exports totaled 25.4 billion U.S. dollars in
the second quarter. California is the nation's leading exporter,
and merchandise shipments account for more than 10 percent of the
state's economic growth. 
</P>
