<HEADLINE> New Air-Traffic Control Center for Pearl River Delta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A new air-traffic control
center for the Pearl River Delta that had been shifted from
Shenzhen to Zhuhai, two cities in south China's Guangdong Province,
was put into operation on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The air space over the Pearl River Delta is one of the busiest
air-traffic zones in China.
</P>
<P>
The new air-traffic control center at Zhuhai, equipped with the
latest technology and neighboring Macao, is responsible for air
traffic covering an area of 16,100 sq km that includes Shenzhen,
Macao, Zhuhai and two heliports, for the time being. The facility
is capable of providing service to and guiding well over 300
planes daily.
</P>
<P>
The new air-traffic control center will make sure that best
service possible is provided for the special planes arriving to
attend the grand ceremony celebrating the return of Macao to China
on December 20.  
</P>
</TEXT>
