<HEADLINE> Nepal, Singapore to Cooperate in Service Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Nepal is going to join hands
with Singapore on human resource development for service industry,
The Kathmandu Post reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The post quoted Narendra Bajracharya, first vice president of
Hotel Association Nepal (HAN) as saying that Singapore Hotel
Association is going to support a one-year diploma program in
hotel management in Nepal, which is to begin from the third week
of September.
</P>
<P>
Bajracharya, who returned home from a 15-day seminar on Hotel
and Catering Management held in Nadi, Fiji, said that due to lack
of well-trained staff, particularly in the hotel industry, quality
of service is deteriorating in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, in a changed globalized context, emerging tourism
industry is seeking efficient personnel along with new
technologies, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bajracharya presented a working paper in the seminar. The paper
contained various issues on tourism industry, including service
quality improvement, human resource development, quality check
ups, upgrading existing facility, prevention of anti-social
activities, environment protection, ecology, licensing, consumer
protection act and so on. 
</P>
