<HEADLINE> Chinese President Leaves on Visit to Three Asian-Pacific Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua)-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
left here this morning on a state visit to Thailand, Australia and
New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The President was invited by Thai King Bhumibol Adulyadej,
Australian Governor-General William Patrick Deane, and New Zealand
Governor-General Michael Hardie Boys.
</P>
<P>
He will also attend the 7th Informal Leadership Meeting of the
Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) to be held in Auckland,
New Zealand, on September 12-13 at the invitation of Jenny Shipley,
Prime Minister of New Zealand, the host of this year's APEC forum.
</P>
<P>
