<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Handles Record Number of Passengers in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
handled a record number of passengers in August this year,
according to latest figures released by the airport authorities.
</P>
<P>
More than 257,600 passengers used the airport last month, the
biggest monthly figure since the airport went into operation four
years ago.
</P>
<P>
From January to August, the airport handled more than 1.75
million passengers, an increase of 21 percent over the same period
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The increase is believed to be partly the result of more
personnel exchanges between Macao and the mainland areas of China
as Macao is returning to the motherland at the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
However, cargo transportation at the airport in August
plummeted by 34 percent from the same month of last year. The
airport witnessed booming cargo business in the summer of 1998 as
something was wrong with the new airport in neighboring Hong Kong.
</P>
</TEXT>
