<HEADLINE> Pinochet's Health Deteriorating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A collaborator of Chile's
former leader, Augusto Pinochet, said on Wednesday that the health
of the former head of state is deteriorating and that he may die
in London.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, who is 83 years old, arrived at a London clinic on
Tuesday in his wheelchair, where he underwent another medical
examination, TV news reports said.
</P>
<P>
Director of the Augusto Pinochet Foundation, Luis Cortes Villa,
who is in London visiting the ex-military chief, told Chilean
reporters in a telephone interview that Pinochet perceives his
death to be close at hand.
</P>
<P>
He said that Pinochet's health has been undermined by months of
detention, but his mental state is normal.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, who had ruled Chile from 1973 to 1990, is Chile's
lifetime Senator.
</P>
<P>
Cortes said that Pinochet is opposed to being released on
humanitarian grounds.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was detained on October 16, 1998, at the request of a
Spanish judge, who accused him of killing and torturing of
political opponents during his military regime.
</P>
<P>
The extradition process of Pinochet will begin at the end of
this month.
</P>
<P>
According to recent medical examinations, Pinochet is suffering
from prostate gland disorder and heart disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
