<HEADLINE> India's Imports Rise Slightly in April-July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- India's imports were
estimated at 14.07 billion U.S. dollars in April-July, up by only
1.01 percent from the level of 13.93 billion U.S. dollars recorded
a year ago.
</P>
<P>
According to the commerce ministry, oil imports during the
period stood at 2754.53 million U.S. dollars, 51.05 percent higher
than last year's 1923.58 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
