<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0294 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Senator Starts Cuba Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The United States Democratic
Senator Sanfod Bishop arrived here Wednesday for a rapprochement
between his country and Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Bishop, from Georgia State, is the third U.S. congressman
visiting the island.
</P>
<P>
Another two Democratic U.S. congressmen, Dannice Davis from
Illinois and Tom Lampson from Texas, arrived Sunday. They are
continuing their visits here as the heads of two separate missions.
</P>
<P>
All the three delegations are scheduled to meet Cuban National
Assembly President Ricardo Alarcon later Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Bishop told reporters upon his arrival that he will make
efforts to increase the understanding and to find a common ground
for the two countries during his four-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban authorities said that the U.S. blockade imposed since
1962 has caused Cuba 60 million U.S. dollars of economic loss.
</P>
<P>
Cuba and the United States have no diplomatic relations for
nearly four decades, but maintain a migratory accord since May
1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
