<HEADLINE> Iran Seeks Further Development of Ties with EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Iranian Foreign
Minister Kamal Kharrazi on Wednesday expressed hope for further
development in his country's relations with the European Union (EU)
.
</P>
<P>
Iran would like to hold another round of talks with the EU
within the current Finnish term of the rotating EU presidency in
order to improve bilateral ties, Kharrazi told a press conference
after meeting with his Finnish counterpart Tarja Halonen.
</P>
<P>
"We have made progress in talks with the European Union. Our
two sides set up working panels discussing issues include energy,
environment, drugs, industry and investment. We just hope all
these will lead up to the signing of agreements eventually," said
the Iranian foreign minister, who arrived here Wednesday for a two-
day visit.
</P>
<P>
Halonen said that she is satisfied with the improvement
achieved in cooperation between Iran and the EU.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, the two ministers focused on issues
including the Middle East peace process, arms control, human
rights and the EU dialogue with the Islamic world.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-EU ties bottomed with the EU members withdrawing
their ambassadors in 1997 summer when Tehran protested over a
German court verdict linking Iranian top leaders with a terrorist
bombing in a Berlin restaurant several years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister is scheduled to meet with Finnish
President Martti Ahtisaari, parliament speaker Riita Uosukainen
and Foreign Trade Minister Kimmo Sasi on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
