<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Host Int'l Construction Fair, Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka is to host South
Asia's first international exhibition and conference on the
construction industry in November, organizers said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The event "Build Int Asia'99" between November 9 and 12 will
provide a unique opportunity for potential investors in
construction and real estate as well as buyers and sellers in
these sectors, said a spokesman for the organizers.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition and conference are supported by the government
and promoted by JPR International (Pvt.) Ltd., a recently
incorporated professional exhibition and convention organizer.
</P>
<P>
The events are expected to bring more than 250 local and
foreign exhibitors and over 40,000 visitors, the spokesman said,
adding that they have sought the assistance of 42 Sri Lankan
missions overseas to help create awareness about the event and
promote participation.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the exhibition and conference is "Homes for the
People and Land for Urban Development."
</P>
<P>
As the Sri Lankan government plans to build 10,000 flats for
slum and shanty dwellers, a huge market for suppliers is expected
to open up and large areas of urban land will be released for
development.
</P>
<P>
The visitors expected to the event include construction sector
professionals such as civil engineers, interior designers,
contractors, builders and architects and students and the general
public.
</P>
<P>
The conference, scheduled for November 10, will be attended by
international and local speakers who will review, assess and
promote future policies and strategies in urban development,
housing and construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
