<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Talented Huis Good Business People (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China's reform and opening up
policies which were introduced at the end of 1978 provided
opportunities for the country's Moslem Hui ethnic people, well-
known for being smart business people and brought their talents
into full play.
</P>
<P>
Ma Xuegui, a Hui farmer in Laoheqiao Village of Lingwu City in
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, sells over 1,000
kg of mutton and beef wholesale to Tianjin and Beijing every day.
</P>
<P>
Ma currently earns 50,000 yuan (about 6,024 U.S. dollars) a
year and has just built a new two-story house to replace his
former mud and brick hut. His five-member family now has all the
popular modern household appliances and a car.
</P>
<P>
"It's the policy of the market economy that has made me
affluent," Ma said with emotion. Before he started as a
businessman in the late 1980s, the annual income of Ma's family
was about 1,000 yuan (about 120 U.S. dollars ) a year from a small
plot of land.
</P>
<P>
The Laoheqiao market, which was formed on the basis of the
village 14 years ago, is now China's largest mutton and beef
wholesale market for Moslems.
</P>
<P>
Every year, about 35,000 sheep, 30,000 cows and nearly 400
camels are slaughtered in the market, and nearly 300 Huis are
engaged in this work.
</P>
<P>
The Huis are descendants of Arabs and Persians who came to
China to trade after the seventh century. There are now some 9
million in China, and nearly 2 million live in Ningxia.
</P>
<P>
The Huis are well-known for being good at business. However,
business was usually looked down upon in ancient times. Before the
founding of new China in 1949, the Huis were not even recognized
by the rulers as an ethnic group.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0323 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile's Copper Production Surges 20 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO September 1 (Xinhua) -- Chile's copper production has
reached 2.156 million tons this year, a 20.2 percent increase over
the same period of last year, Chile's Copper Commission said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The copper production of Chile, the world's first copper
producer and exporter, in 1998 stood at 3.689 million tons, and
the copper giant is expected to produce over 4 million tons by the
end of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0324 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Talented Huis Good Business People (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's reform and opening up policies encouraged many Huis to
engage in business to secure a better living.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays in Tongxin County, the most populous county in Ningxia,
one-third of the Hui people are engaged in various kinds of
businesses. In Xihaigu Prefecture, the poorest area of the region,
even women of the Hui nationality, who are used to being confined
to their homes, are now actively engaged in business, and half of
the prefecture's 200,000 Hui ethnic business women have become
affluent.
</P>
<P>
Thus far, Ningxia has set up over 300 commodity markets and
over 1,000 various kinds of specialized markets and trading
agencies, with business turnover exceeding over 4 billion yuan (
about 480 million U.S. dollars) a year.
</P>
<P>
The number of the region's individual and privately owned
enterprises now has reached nearly 100,000, employing over 170,000
people.
</P>
<P>
Jingyuan County at the foot of Liupan Mountain, where Hui
ethnic people make up for 96 percent of the local population, has
been built into one of the country's key cow-breeding bases.
</P>
<P>
A meat processing plant has been built which slaughters 15,000
cows and process 1,800 tons of beef and related products a year.
At present, the output of animal husbandry accounts for one-third
of Ningxia's agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
After years of development, many Hui entrepreneurs have emerged,
and the region's first listed company, the Ningxia Minzu
Petrochemical Group, is now the largest dicyandiamide production
base in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia also has become one of the world's three major tantalum
production bases. Four of every ten mobile phones in the world are
manufactured with products produced by the Ningxia Nonferrous
Metal Smeltery.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia now also has established trade and economic cooperation
ties with more than 60 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0325 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province to Hold Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Province in east China
is planning an economic and trade fair from October 9 to 12 in the
city of Liaocheng to help the western part of the province to
attract more domestic and overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The largest project available reportedly will need one billion
yuan (about 120 million U.S. dollars) worth of investment.
</P>
<P>
There will be a symposium on agricultural development,
scientific and technological cooperation, urban construction, as
part of the fair.
</P>
<P>
Liaocheng is a communications hub. The Beijing-Kowloon railway
line runs through it and there is an expressway to Jinan, the
capital of Shandong.
</P>
<P>
The past few years saw an average annual economic growth rate
of 30 percent of the city. It is China's largest processor of the
donkey-hide gelatin, a traditional Chinese medicine, with its
output accounting for 70 percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The city is also an important grain, cotton, vegetable, and
sideline produce center and its beef exports ranked first in
Shandong and chicken exports, second.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0326 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNCTAD Hails China As Model Developing Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China has been a successful
model of development with its economic reforms over the past two
decades, Rubens Ricupero, Secretary-General of the United Nations
Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD), said in a recent
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He said China's economic achievements since the founding of the
republic 50 years ago and particularly since its implementation of
the opening-up policy some 20 years ago have enhanced the
confidence of other developing countries in seeking their own
social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
With an annual economic increase of 9.8 percent in the past 20
years, China is one of the few dynamic economies in the world with
both rapid and sustained growth, Ricupero said.
</P>
<P>
In foreign trade, China's annual exports have shot up to 184
billion U.S. dollars from only 1 billion dollars in 1979.
According to the 1998 ranking list by the World Trade Organization
(WTO), China was the world's fifth largest exporter and sixth
largest importer.
</P>
<P>
Ricupero said that he was deeply impressed with the speed of
the foreign direct investment (FDI) inflows into China. Some 20
years ago, he recalled, the FDI to China was nearly zero. But the
latest UNCTAD report showed that China has been the top FDI
recipient among developing countries since 1992. By June 1999,
China has received a total of 286 billion dollars worth of the FDI.
</P>
<P>
"Facts and figures speak louder than words," said Ricupero. "It
's almost unnecessary to make further comments."
</P>
<P>
As the only permanent member from the developing world in the
UN Security Council, Ricupero said that China is the most reliable
supporter for any UN policy about the promotion of the development
of developing countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the step-by-step way in which China has been
carrying out its economic reforms in accordance with its own
circumstances has not only set a good example for other developing
countries but also contributed to the whole international
community.
</P>
<P>
Ricupero said that he is pleased with his organization's close
and cooperative relationship with China. As the UNCTAD chief, he
paid several visits to China and witnessed China's amazing changes
brought by the reforms.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident in China's economic prospects," he said, noting
that it would still be deemed a great success if China could keep
its growth rate at 6-7 percent following a continuous annual
growth of about 10 percent during the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Ricupero said that the next century is a knowledge-based
century and that he hopes China would make further efforts to
strengthen education and improve the quality of its massive labor
force to create more favorable conditions to compete in the 21st
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
