<HEADLINE> Comets, Liberty Open WNBA Finals on Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Houston Comets and New
York Liberty renew acquaintances Thursday night when they battle
in Game One of the best-of-three WNBA Finals at Madison Square
Garden here.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time in three years these teams are meeting
for the title. Houston gained the first of its two straight
championships with a victory over New York in a one-game series 65-
51 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
These clubs split two games this season with the home team
winning each time. Houston leads the all-time series 6-4 and holds
a 4-1 mark home-court record. New York's only triumph came in its
first visit on June 26. 1997.
</P>
<P>
Houston is paced by two-time regular season and playoff MVP
Cynthia Cooper. She scored 23 points and dished out a postseason
record 12 assists in the clinching game over the Los Angeles
Sparks for the Western Conference title. Sheryl Swoopes also added
23 points.
</P>
<P>
New York got here on the strength of its Eastern Conference
finals win over the Charlotte Sting in three games. Teresa
Weatherspoon personally carried the club to victory.
</P>
<P>
She averaged 12.5 points during the two victories in New York
and made sure the raucous home crowd stayed that way throughout
the series.
</P>
<P>
The home team is 4-0 all-time in the finals and the last three
best-of-three series have seen the home club win each time. The
next two contests are in Houston. Game Two is Saturday and Game
Three, if necessary, is Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
