<HEADLINE> Turkey be Treated as Prospective EU Member: Dini </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini on Wednesday expressed that Turkey should be treated as a
prospective European Union (EU) member.
</P>
<P>
In a speech to Italian ambassadors recalled for an annual
conference here, Dini said that EU must "cover a great
Mediterranean country like Turkey" and should not put off "
recognition of its status as a candidate for membership."
</P>
<P>
He added that the EU should recognize Ankara as a formal
candidate at its upcoming December meeting in Helsinki.
</P>
<P>
At its summit last year, the EU decided that six countries --
Poland, the Czech Republic, Slovenia, Estonia, Hungary and Cyprus -
- would be its new members and five others would then follow with
Turkey at the bottom of the list.  
