Governor General of Canada Romeo LeBlanc.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien received Chirac later in
the day at Parliament Hill, where the two leaders discussed
bilateral relations and international issues including the
situation in the Balkans, the conflict in the Great Lakes region
of Africa, as well as the peace prospects for the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is scheduled to leave for French speaking Quebec City to
continue his visit Thursday when he will attend the celebration of
the 20th anniversary of the International Association of
Francophone Mayors.
</P>
