<HEADLINE> All Africa Games Village Officially Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- South African Sports
Minister Ngconde Balfour Wednesday officially opened the All
Africa Games Village in Alexandra, north of Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
The village, comprising 1,700 houses, a primary school and a
shopping center, will house athletes for the All Africa Games due
to start next week.
</P>
<P>
Balfour appealed to the residents of Alexandra to help host a
peaceful and crime-free event.
</P>
<P>
"I believe you will live up to our reputation of hospitality",
he told residents attending the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Balfour said he believed the All Africa Games would prove to
the international community that South Africa could successfully
host such an event.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is bidding to host the 2006 soccer world cup
finals.
</P>
<P>
The black township of Alexandra is one of the three most
dangerous areas in Johannesburg, the world's "capital of crimes".
</P>
<P>
After the games, the athletes' village will be transferred to
the local community as a means of poverty alleviation. 
</P>
