<HEADLINE> Juninho on Way Back to Middlesbrough </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Middlesbrough have signed their
former midfielder Juninho on loan until the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
According to the BBC report on Wednesday, the deal was
announced after manager Bryan Robson flew to Spain to seal the
transfer with the Brazilian's club, Atletico Madrid.
</P>
<P>
On a busy day in the transfer market at the Riverside, Boro
also signed 26-year-old Senegal midfielder Ibrahim Ba on a
contract until the end of the season from AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
A club spokesman said: "A deal has been agreed with Atletico
Madrid which will see Juninho join Middlesbrough on a short-term
contract until June 2000 with a view to the player being offered
an extended contract after that time.
</P>
<P>
"The deal is subject to Juninho being granted a work permit and
the club has already made an application to the Department for
Education and Employment.
</P>
<P>
"Juninho will not come to Teesside until the result of the
application is known."
</P>
<P>
Juninho fell out of favor with Atletico Madrid, the club he
joined two years ago in a 12 million pound deal from Middlesbrough.
</P>
<P>
A broken leg dashed his hopes of playing for Brazil in the 1998
World Cup in France.
</P>
<P>
He returned to the Atletico side last season but has not been
in favor with the Spanish club's new coach, Claudio Ranieri.
</P>
<P>
"Bringing Juninho back to Middlesbrough is great news for
Teesside and I am sure our fans will be delighted," said chief
executive Keith Lamb.
</P>
<P>
"He was a massive success during his 18 months with us and we
hardly need to explain why we want to put him back in a
Middlesbrough shirt.
</P>
<P>
"Juninho is the sort of player who will add quality to the
entire Premier League. His record as being selected as the Carling
Premiership Player of the Year in 1997 speaks for itself.
</P>
<P>
"While our own fans chose him as the greatest player in
Middlesbrough's history."
</P>
<P>
Lamb added: "Ibrahim Ba is another world class player, who cost
Milan 8m only a couple of years ago.
</P>
<P>
"Bryan Robson has been an admirer of his skills for a long time
and I am sure he will be an excellent addition to our first team
squad." 
</P>
</TEXT>
