<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Monarchs Forward Griffith Wins WNBA MVP Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The season may have ended on
a bitter note for Sacramento Monarchs forward-center Yolanda
Griffith,but she has the WNBA Most Valuable Player award to lift
her spirits.
</P>
<P>
Griffith, who won the Newcomer and Defensive Player of the Year
awards last Thursday, officially added the marquee MVP award to
the collection, ending the two-year reign of Houston Comets guard
Cynthia Cooper.
</P>
<P>
Griffith received 397 points and 23 first-place votes from a
panel of sportswriters and broadcasters. Forward Sheryl Swoopes of
the Comets finished second with 364 points and 15 first-place
votes,followed by Cooper, who had 324 points and 13 first-place
votes.
</P>
<P>
Griffith led the league in rebounding (11.8), steals (2.52) and
double-doubles (17), ranked second in scoring (18.8) and field
goal percentage (.541)and was third in blocked shots (1.86).
</P>
<P>
The awards brighten an otherwise upsetting end to the season
for Griffith, who missed the last four games with a torn medial
meniscus in her right knee. The Monarchs dropped all four of those
contests, including a 71-58 loss to Los Angeles last week in a one-
game playoff.
</P>
<P>
Once the American Basketball Leauge went defunct, Griffith
entered the WNBA draft and was selected by Sacramento second
overall after the Washington Mystics took Chamique Holdsclaw.
</P>
<P>
Griffith was recently named to the 1999-2000 Women's National
Team by USA Basketball, joining teammate Ruthie Bolton-Holifield.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990902.0355 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Foreign Ministry Sets Up Reform's Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Providing an adequate response to
the growing demand for foreign policy as a service and support for
Italy as a "country-system" on the world stage is the main goals
in the Italian foreign ministry reform to go into effect next
year, the ministry's secretary-general Umberto Vattani said
Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to Italian news agency Ansa, at the opening day of
the 2-day Italian ambassadors conference, Vattani said that the
growing need for Italian foreign policy derives from three
factors: crises laden with risk for Italy; Europe's growth and its
increasing role in the daily life of Italians; and
internationalization to a series of economic and social sectors
whence a pressing demand for the related services.
</P>
<P>
Vattani said the response must be a "global diplomacy" equipped
with the most modern tools, in which the foreign ministry is at
the cutting edge in the public administration, and above all a
rational and effective organization of the ministry's work.
</P>
<P>
Novelties to come on stream on January 1 include the Council
for International Affairs, chaired by the foreign minister and his
deputies with the aim of structuring and making systematic work at
the ministry's summit on elaborating and conducting foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
Another novelty is the ministry's organization by geographical
area, although issues of European integration will be handled by a
single division.
</P>
<P>
There will also be a new analysis and planning unit which will
extend the time horizon of Italian diplomacy so that its diplomats
"propose and act" rather than simply reacting to the development
of events.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
